    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dd7ab832_9f3e43a2",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/event-capturer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 20
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-02-16T23:19:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m a little uncomfortable with this usage.\n\nstd::list doesn\u0027t invalidate other iterators when you erase an element, but this isn\u0027t true of other list-like types (std::vector).\n\nI think this is a potential subtle pitfall if someone tries to replace list --\u003e vector.\n\n(I\u0027d be satisfied by a unit-test that tests this particular behavior)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "b2c03cf43d66463647ff05faa79d8d71b726ed3b",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dd255844_5cf3f190",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/event-capturer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 20
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-02-17T06:21:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That is the correct way to do this. I stepped in the trap of using vector in the initial version. \nUnfortunately, we don\u0027t have unit tests for *any* of the UI/Qt code, which is terrible. I have no idea why this is the case and think it should be addressed, but it\u0027s beyond the scope of this change.\nI have added a comment to the header cautioning against using a different container.",
      "parentUuid": "dd7ab832_9f3e43a2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 22
